Comment: Various examples of completion: ɓa-ɬaβih 'finish bathing'; ɓa-wahuʔu 'finish weeding garden/field'; ɓa-ɓu 'finish eating'; hoi-ra-ni 'a finished construction'.
ɗin̉-to-kʷi is a 'fast runner'. Also cf. 'hasten, hurry' 14.230.
Means 'right now'. Also no-ko-wa 'now or shortly'. Also see 'soon' 14.351.
From Span. 'cinco'. Numbers 'five' and above are borrowed from Span.
siɬ-kʷa is a 'hole in the ground'.
Means, e.g. 'cross to the other side of a river or lake'.
Also ya-pa-na 'as far as it goes'. See also ya- 'end, limit indicator' in 'bottom' 12.340; 'last' 13.350; and 'end (temporal)' 14. 260.
The morpheme ya- means 'end limit indicator'.
Refers to a thing in view of the speaker.
Drive from behind, i.e. 'herd', used of children or animals. tuka-boh is 'pilot a canoe'.
Also poʔmo 'to rise'. See also ta-ra 04.630 'to awaken and rise'.
Also sa-pil-čo 'turn completely around'; βol-ye 'turn the head'; ha-pil-na 'turn in a circle' 12.820.
Lit. 'to put up' or 'cause to stand'. Also roya-tiʔi 'house-building'.
Used for a person. Also ɗoʔ-si 'stoop'.
Lit. 'to scatter'. wul-a-ɗi 'plant seed' is the most common. Also ta-mol-na 'to extend'; pasin̉-na 'spread out' 09.340, are used to express 'sowing seed'. Also see 'plant' 08.531.
Means 'space'. Also son̉-čo means a separate room.
Also roya, which can be unoccupied or unpossessed, in contrast to as-na.
No generic term. Lit, 'motacú (palm)' + -mo 'nut/fruit'. Other varieties: nihnaiwam-mo 'chonta nut'; purun̉-mo 'totaí nut'.
Also inˀ-na 'mix (pouring or running together)'; tau-na 'mix (by beating)'.
ta-raɬ-ni is 'healed, cured'; se-hau-ni is 'better (but not completely cured)'.
This appears to be a generic term. Other varieties are huɗi 'howler m.'; ɗespuh 'night m.'; kačiči 'whistler m.'; patore 'spider m.'.
No generic term for 'owl'. Other varieties are: bayamespa; tukuku; wohnapa.
No generic term for 'parrot'. Other varieties are: sikʷiʔla; čeleka; karaʔa; čawan̉; seyamo; čitan̉; raweʔe; seʔle-seʔle; awaro.
Lit. 'time of lowering river level'. Cf. 'summer' 14.760.
Lit. 'loud sound'. Also ɓei-sineɬ 'faint sound'; čon-sineɬ 'true sound' or 'the Movima language.'
I. e. 'with interest'. Cf. 'look (but not necessarily with interest)' βay-e-ɬe; and 'see (and understand)' 15.510.
Also wa-čo-ye, used of a person.
Also ilim-ni 'clear (transparent)'; čoi-rei 'surely (plainly understood)'. Also cf. 'sure' 17.370.
Also means 'way, manner'. Intonation signals question.
Also itanaʔa 'one with foreign sounding speech'.
